subsection.p:
The vector that has the same magnitude as {\bf{v}} but the opposite direction is called the oppositeopposite vectorvectoropposite of {\bf{v}} and denoted by {-\bf{v}}.  Then
  {\bf{v}}+{-\bf{v}}={\bf{0}}   
  If the sum of the forces acting on an object is {\bf{0}}, the forces are said to be in equilibriumequilibrium, and the object will remain stationary.

assemblage.p:
The vector
  {\bf{v}} = a{\bf{i}} + b{\bf{j}}
is the vector whose horizontal component is a and whose vertical component is b.

Suppose that the vector {\bf{v}} has magnitude \|{\bf{v}}\| and points in the direction of the angle \theta in standard position. If {\bf{v}} has the coordinate form {\bf{v}} = a{\bf{i}} + b{\bf{j}}, then

    a \amp = \|{\bf{v}}\| \cos \theta  \amp \amp \amp    \|{\bf{v}}\| \amp = \sqrt{a^2 + b^2}
    b \amp = \|{\bf{v}}\| \sin \theta  \amp \amp  \amp    \tan \theta \amp = \dfrac{b}{a}
